üõ†Ô∏è Step-by-Step Solution for Day 18: Create Read-Only IAM Policy (iampolicy_ravi)
Follow these exact steps to create a custom IAM policy that grants read-only access to the EC2 console.

Login to the AWS Console

Open a web browser.

Go to the provided Console URL: https://386532143645.signin.aws.amazon.com/console?region=us-east-1

Enter the provided credentials:

Username: kk_labs_user_862309

Password: wrC5IpCOgF3L

Click Sign In.

Navigate to the IAM Service

Once logged in, use the top search bar to find "IAM" and click on it.

Go to the Policies Page

In the left-hand navigation menu, click on "Policies" (under "Access management").

Start Creating a New Policy

On the Policies page, click the "Create policy" button.

Step 1: Define Permissions (Visual Editor)

Select a Service: Click on "Choose a service" and select "EC2".

Select Actions:

Click on "Select actions".

In the filter/search box, type "Describe". This will show all read-only actions.

Expand the "Read" access level section. Check the boxes next to:

DescribeInstances

DescribeImages (this covers AMIs)

DescribeSnapshots

(Optionally, you can click the checkbox for the entire "Read" access level to select all read actions, but the three above are the minimum for the lab requirement).

Specify Resources: Leave this as the default "All resources".

Click the blue "Next" button.

Step 2: Review and Finalize Policy

On this page, you will name and review your policy.

Policy Name: Enter iampolicy_ravi.

Description (Optional): You can enter "Read-only access to EC2 instances, AMIs, and snapshots."

Review the Policy summary on the right. It should show the three actions you selected for all resources.

Scroll to the bottom and click the orange "Create policy" button.

Verification (Final Step)

You will see a green success banner: "Policy iampolicy_ravi created successfully."

You will be redirected to the list of policies.

Use the search bar at the top of the policies list and type iampolicy_ravi.

Verify that your new custom policy appears in the results.

Task Complete! ‚úÖ You have successfully created the custom IAM policy iampolicy_ravi.

